 We are seeking a skilled
 **Manual Tester** 
 responsible for ensuring application quality, reliability, and performance through structured test planning, execution, and defect management. The role involves analyzing business requirements and design documents to create effective test scenarios, preparing and executing test cases, and performing various testing types such as functional, regression, integration, system, UAT, and smoke/sanity testing. The tester will log and track defects using tools like JIRA, ALM, Bugzilla, or Azure DevOps, collaborate with developers and stakeholders to resolve issues, and ensure comprehensive test coverage and compliance with QA standards. Additional responsibilities include preparing test reports, monitoring execution status, participating in review meetings and sprint ceremonies, and supporting application releases across environments. Required skills include a strong understanding of SDLC/STLC, proficiency with test management tools (JIRA, TestRail, HP ALM, Zephyr), ability to write clear test cases, SQL knowledge for backend validation, and experience in Agile/Scrum environments. Strong analytical, problem\\-solving, communication, and documentation skills are essential. Good\\-to\\-have skills include basic API testing knowledge (Postman), exposure to automation concepts (Selenium, Python, Java), telecom domain experience, and familiarity with performance or security testing basics.
